observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Property and the Accounting Units agreed to:
a. Re-classify each PPE item in the inventory report according to PPE classification per the Electronic-New Government Accounting System or e-NGAS;
b. Indicate or assign a property number on each existing and newly acquired PPE property number in the e-NGAs;
c. Provide and attach a property sticker to each PPE accounted; and
d. Implement the necessary procedural guidelines outlined in COA Circular No. 2020-006 to address the unrecorded and over-recorded properties thereby reconciling both property records.

We recommended that the City, through the City Assessor, engage the services of a government financial institution or an accredited independent appraiser to appropriately appraise the value of the land, crops and trees, and improvements affected by their infrastructure projects in accordance with the rules and regulations;
The City Legal Officer review the waiver or quitclaim executed by the land owners as it does not include conditions on the payment of the value of affected land;
The City Accountant require that pictures of crops, trees, and improvements are included as supporting documents in the compensation payments; and
The City Mayor require the City Engineer’s Office (CEO) to render an inventory report on the cut-down trees recovered.

We recommended that:  
The City Accountant immediately transfer the unexpended/unobligated balance of CY 2018 QRF and DRRMF-MOOE to the Trust Fund Books for easy monitoring of the utilization and to ensure the availability of this fund to support disaster risk reduction and management activities;  
The City Disaster and Risk Reduction Management Council consider in the formulation of disaster risk reduction management programs/projects/activities the previous year's unexpended balance of LDRRMF to attain maximum utilization of the fund;  
The LGU reverts the CY 2011 and 2012 unutilized LDRRMF to the General Fund for other social services of the City; and  
The City Accountant appropriately disclose the amount and details of the CO-continuing appropriation in the Notes to Financial Statements for proper monitoring and utilization of the fund.

We recommended that the Accounting Office and the City General Services Office to:  
Regularly update the Equipment Ledger Cards and Property Cards on each property;  
Re-classify each PPE items in the inventory report according to PPE classification per Electronic-New Government Accounting System or E-NGAS;  
Indicate or assign a property number on each PPE items according to the PPE property number in E-NGAS;  
Provide and attach property sticker to each PPE item;  
Undertake the required reconciliation of property records under Section 114 of Manual on NGAS, Volume I and effect the necessary adjustments to have a reliable balance of said accounts in the financial statement; and  
Investigate the noted difference and if found out that these properties are missing, demand the appropriate payment/s from person/s accountable thereof.

We recommended that the City General Services Office to:

Regularly maintain an updated Property Cards on each property;
Re-classify each PPE items in the inventory report according to PPE classification per Electronic-New Government Accounting System or E-NGAS;

Indicate or assign a property number on each PPE items according to the PPE property number in E-NGAS;
Provide and attach property sticker to each PPE item;
Undertake the required
reconciliation of property records pursuant to Section 114 of MNGAS, Volume I and effect the necessary adjustments in order to have reliable balances of said accounts in the financial statement; and 

Investigate the noted difference and if found out that these properties are missing, demand the appropriate payment/s from person/s accountable thereof.

We recommended that:
The City Accountant immediately transfer the unexpended/unobligated balance of CY 2018 QRF and DRRMF-MOOE to the Trust Fund Books for easy monitoring of the utilization and to ensure the availability of this fund to support disaster risk reduction and management activities;
The City Disaster and Risk Reduction Management Council consider in the formulation of disaster risk reduction management programs/projects/activities the previous year's unexpended balance of LDRRMF to attain maximum utilization of the fund;
The LGU reverts back the CY 2011 and 2012 unutilized LDRRMF to the General Fund for other social services of the City; and
The City Accountant appropriately disclose the amount and details of the CO-continuing appropriation in the Notes to Financial Statements for proper monitoring and utilization of the fund.

We recommended that the Accounting Office and the City General Services Office to:

Regularly update the Equipment Ledger Cards and Property Cards on each property;
Re-classify each PPE items in the inventory report according to PPE classification per Electronic-New Government Accounting System or E-NGAS;
Indicate or assign a property number on each PPE items according to the PPE property number in E-NGAS;
Provide and attach property sticker to each PPE item;
Undertake the required reconciliation of property records pursuant to Section 114 of Manual on NGAS, Volume I and effect the necessary adjustments in order to have a reliable balance of said accounts in the financial statement; and
Investigate the noted difference and if found out that these properties are missing, demand the appropriate payment/s from person/s accountable thereof.

We recommended that:

The City Accountant or the agency’s authorized representative to submit to COA-ATL the DVs covering the cash advances for confidential/intelligence purposes within seven (7) days after the release of checks as prescribed in Section 6.1.8.4 of Joint Circular No. 2015-01;

The City Accountant to require from the Accountable Officer the required supporting documents related to P2,310,000.00 cash advances drawn in CY 2017 for confidential/intelligence fund, and to henceforth ensure that all the required supporting documents enumerated in the checklist of Annex D be attached in the DV upon submission to COA-ATL; 

The agency through the City Budget Officer to make sure that the Confidential Fund will not exceed 30% of the total annual allocation for LGU’s Peace and Order Program in conformity with the Joint Circular; and

Revisit the provisions of Joint Circular No. 2015-01 for guidance in the disbursement of Confidential Fund.

We recommended that:
The City Mayor and GSO to scrutinize and evaluate carefully the purchase requests on repair of heavy equipment to ensure the necessity of repair;

The City Mayor  exercise due care and prudence in the disbursements of funds to avoid excessive expenditures;

Henceforth, avoid spending government funds without observing the proper disbursement procedures in compliance with existing laws, rules and regulations; and

The City GSO to exert effort in securing the OR/CR and other pertinent documents of the heavy equipment to facilitate the immediate insurance of said property with GSIS pursuant to Section 5 of RA No. 656.

